The paper focuses on visual object tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves optimizing a convolutional layer with Gradient Descent, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of hard negative mining, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed algorithm on a benchmark dataset, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) research.
